Key Match Events: The Phoenix Suns defeated the Utah Jazz 114-106.
Devin Booker, Kevin Durant, and Bradley Beal played until the final seconds due to the close competition.
The Jazz had a poor shooting performance, going 9-of-42 from 3-point range.
Post-Match Reflections: Utah Jazz head coach Will Hardy reflected on the team's poor shooting night and expressed that if they played the same way again, they might have won.
Hardy noted that the Jazz won the possession game, points in the paint, and second chance points despite the loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rookie Cody Williams had his best game of the season, scoring 13 points with two rebounds and two assists in front of his family and friends.
Jordan Clarkson joined the broadcast team during the second quarter, providing insights and cheering on his teammates.
Sideline reporter Lauren Green interviewed Perry High School coach Sam Duane, who spoke about his pride in Cody Williams' performance.
